						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in the Lakshmīnārāyaṇasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Achyuta, 1542 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1464, Śubhakṛit, Chaitra ba. 6, Wednesday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1542 A.D., April 5.</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers the remission of taxes on marriages and the taxes on the earnings of Brāhmaṇas for the merit of the king. Rāmābhaṭlayya issued the orders and Peddirājayya conveyed them to the Reḍḍis and Karaṇams of the village of Krottacheruvu.</p>						

						</summary>
